</p>


<p>
<b>Regrade Policy:</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Your exams and homeworks will be graded using <a href="https://gradescope.com/" target="_blank">Gradescope</a>.
 &nbsp;You will be able to request regrades <b><i>directly from your TA</i></b> through Gradescope for a specified window of time.
  &nbsp;Be sure to make your request within the specified window of time; no regrade requests will be accepted after the
   deadline. <b>Note:</b> Your grader will consider your regrade request only if you
			have explained clearly, thoroughly, and politely why you think an error in grading was made.</li>
</li></ul>
</p>


<p><b>Grading:</b> 

  Your cumulative average will be computed as the best of the following weighted averages:
  <ul>
    <li>20% Homework, &nbsp;20% Midterm 1, &nbsp;20% Midterm 2, &nbsp;40% Final Exam</li>
    <li>20% Homework, &nbsp;20% Best midterm, &nbsp;&nbsp;&emsp;&emsp;60% Final Exam</li>
  </ul>
  
</p>



<p>Your course grade will be determined by your cumulative average at the end of the quarter,
and will be based on the following scale:

<center>        
